{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01U3nccGvd2Dj5Nzmayz8mb2","type":"tool_result","content":"  1560→### Patterns to Avoid\n  1561→\n  1562→1. **Stale epic/story specs.** Error counts, file paths, and scope estimates in stories diverged from reality. Stories should be validated against the codebase at creation time.\n  1563→2. **No escalation path for environment blockers.** 14-4 was stuck for 8 sessions with no mechanism to notify a human. Ralph needs a \"needs-human\" status that triggers an alert.\n  1564→3. **Semgrep `...` as literal.** The `...` token in Semgrep is always a metavariable/wildcard, never a literal match for Python Ellipsis. This was a knowledge gap. All existing Semgrep rules should be audited for this misuse.\n  1565→\n  1566→---\n  1567→\n  1568→## 7. Action Items\n  1569→\n  1570→### Fix Now (Before Next Session)\n  1571→\n  1572→| # | Action | Owner |\n  1573→|---|--------|-------|\n  1574→| 1 | Manually verify or descope story 14-4 to close the sprint | Human |\n  1575→| 2 | Decide if sprint is \"done enough\" at 98.5% to close formally | Human |\n  1576→\n  1577→### Fix Soon (Next Sprint)\n  1578→\n  1579→| # | Action | Rationale |\n  1580→|---|--------|-----------|\n  1581→| 3 | Add `needs-human` story status that ralph can set when environment blockers are detected | Prevents stories from silently burning retries for 8 sessions |\n  1582→| 4 | Add HarnessState `opensearch` field to the interface (tech debt from 15-4 cast workaround) | Type safety |\n  1583→| 5 | Audit all Semgrep rules for `...` metavariable misuse (pattern from 15-5) | May have false positives in other rules |\n  1584→| 6 | Validate story specs against codebase at creation time (error counts, file paths) | Prevents scope surprises |\n  1585→\n  1586→### Backlog (Track But Not Urgent)\n  1587→\n  1588→| # | Action | Rationale |\n  1589→|---|--------|-----------|\n  1590→| 7 | Fix Docker credential store for non-interactive sessions | Unblocks Docker-dependent verification in ralph |\n  1591→| 8 | Audit test files for double-cast (`as unknown as T`) patterns — consider vitest helpers | Test code quality |\n  1592→| 9 | Add ralph retry-waste metric (carry forward from prior sessions) | Measure compute spent on stuck stories |\n  1593→| 10 | Investigate `'in-review'` vs `'review'` status inconsistency across bash/yaml/TypeScript layers | Possible latent bug in other system parts |\n  1594→\n  1595→---\n  1596→\n  1597→### Session Velocity (Updated)\n  1598→\n  1599→| Session | Stories Attempted | Stories Completed (done) | Stories Stuck |\n  1600→|---------|-------------------|--------------------------|---------------|\n  1601→| 10 | 4 | 4 | 0 |\n  1602→| 11 | 9 | 6 | 3 (Docker) |\n  1603→| 12 | 1 | 0 | 1 (ENOSPC) |\n  1604→| 13 | 3 | 0 | 3 (Docker) |\n  1605→| 14 | 1 | 1 | 0 (3 skipped) |\n  1606→| 15 | 10 | 6 | 3 (verifying) |\n  1607→| 16 | 1 | 1 | 0 |\n  1608→| 17 | 2 | 2 | 0 |\n  1609→| 18 | 1 | 1 | 0 |\n  1610→| **19** | **0** | **0** | **0 (1 skipped: retry-exhausted)** |\n  1611→\n  1612→### Final Sprint Summary (2026-03-25)\n  1613→\n  1614→**Total stories completed today:** 10 (sessions 10-18)\n  1615→**Sprint completion:** 65/66 (98.5%)\n  1616→**Remaining:** 14-4 (verifying — retry-exhausted, needs human intervention)\n  1617→**Sessions today:** 10 (sessions 10-19)\n  1618→**Epics fully closed:** 0-15 except Epic 14 (1 story stuck)\n  1619→**Recommendation:** Close the sprint. Descope or manually verify 14-4 as a follow-up."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01HMztFBxBukvWNCBRdhHJLr","session_id":"52f9f7f8-e884-4c76-973e-82168b211b16","uuid":"a29d6f0b-b644-49dd-89f8-dd819f275e50","timestamp":"2026-03-25T07:20:33.132Z"}
